HEADWORD: Agincourt
<hw>Agincourt</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a battle in which
English longbowmen under Henry V decisively defeated a much larger
French army in 1415. It was named for the site at which it
occurred.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

